   <body>
      <context>You can deactivate business units to make them unavailable for selection while creating projects and user accounts. Also, a deactivated business unit is unavailable to create a sub-level business unit.</context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click<uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol>page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand<uicontrol>Functional Configurations</uicontrol>, and then click<uicontrol>Business Unit</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>BUSINESS UNIT</uicontrol> list pageis displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the required business unit, and then click<uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Clear the<uicontrol>Is Active</uicontrol> check box.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click<uicontrol>Save</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
